        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 5 at 10:34PM CDT by NWS Bismarck ND</headline>
        <description>At 1033 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Lignite, or 31 miles east of Crosby, moving northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lignite, Portal, Flaxton, and Northgate.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
